cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.NE, cs.SI

The paper proposes a method for automatic PD motor-state assessment using a wrist-worn wearable sensor, which involves machine learning techniques such as convolutional neural networks (CNNs) and class activation map (CAM). This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) as it involves wearable technology and user interaction, Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it uses CNNs for classification, Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) as it involves image analysis techniques, Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) as it involves neural networks, and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) as it involves analyzing data from multiple patients.
